==English==
===Etymology===
Via Middle English and Old French from {{L.}} ''[[instaurare]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A place where items may be stored.
#: ''This building used to be a '''store''' for old tires.''
# A supply held in storage.
#: ''We have a large '''store''' of beer, in case we're snowed in.''
#(''especially US'') A place from which items may be bought.
#: ''I need to get some milk from the grocery '''store'''.''
# {{computing}} {{archaic}} Memory.
#: ''The main '''store''' of 1000 36-bit words seemed large at the time.''

====Synonyms====
*(''place where items may be stored''):
*(''supply held in storage''): [[stock]], [[supply]]
*(''place from which items may be bought''): [[boutique]], [[shop]] (''UK'')
*(''in computing''): [[memory]]

